      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/Search\" title=\"Search\">Search</a> * <a href=\"/Score\" title=\"Score\">Score</a> * Alpha</b>\n</p><p><b>Alpha</b> (α) is the <a href=\"/Lower_Bound\" title=\"Lower Bound\">lower bound</a>, representing the minimum <a href=\"/Score\" title=\"Score\">score</a> that a <a href=\"/Node\" title=\"Node\">node</a> must reach in order to change the value of a previous node. Alpha has the same semantic as max in <a href=\"/Negamax\" title=\"Negamax\">Negamax</a>, and represents the minimum score that the maximizing player is assured of assuming optimal play of both sides. \n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Alpha&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Alpha-Beta\" title=\"Alpha-Beta\">Alpha-Beta</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Beta\" title=\"Beta\">Beta</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Bound\" title=\"Bound\">Bound</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Lower_Bound\" title=\"Lower Bound\">Lower Bound</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Upper_Bound\" title=\"Upper Bound\">Upper Bound</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Exact_Score\" title=\"Exact Score\">Exact Score</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Alpha&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alpha\">Alpha from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alpha_%28disambiguation%29\">Alpha (disambiguation) from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alpha_and_Omega\">Alpha and Omega from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Software_release_life_cycle#Alpha\">Alpha release - Software release life cycle from Wikipedia</a></li></ul>\n<p><b><a href=\"/Score\" title=\"Score\">Up one Level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260301150447\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.003 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.004 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 7/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 12/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key oscar70_mw1-mw_:pcache:idhash:1070-0!canonical and timestamp 20260301150446 and revision id 1368\n -->\n"
